data.name: SABIC's Specialties Business
data.description: SABIC’s Specialties Business produces highly differentiated products which include specialty engineering thermoplastic resins and compounds, composites, additives, and additive manufacturing solutions. With a distinct set of multi-function physical properties to serve a wide range of industries, the branded portfolio offers high heat solutions including ULTEM™, EXTEM™ and SILTEM™ resins, LNP™ resins and compounds, LNP™ PC copolymers, and NORYL™ resins and compounds. SABIC also offers extensive material processing expertise, leveraging its product engineers and global application technology development centers.

data.name: SILTEM™ Resin
data.description: SILTEM™ resin is a high-performance non-fluorinated alternative to flexible fluoropolymers in wire and cable jacketing and tubing applications. Discover its potential to enhance performance without compromising flexibility.

data.name: ULTEM™ Resin
data.description:
Discover range of PEI resins - ULTEM™ resins – amorphous, transparent, polyetherimide starting with ULTEM™ 1000 unreinforced PEI resins, high-performance base material for blends, reinforced grades, offering: long-term high heat capability, dimensional stability, strength and modulus, inherent low FST, non-halogenated FR solution, hydrolytic and chemical stability, IR transparency, stable dielectric properties, lightweight, colorability.

ULTEM™ HU1004 resin, PEI resin blend, healthcare grade well suited for strong, durable medical devices that withstand multiple sterilization methods, offer enhanced hydrolytic stability in steam autoclave sterilization. ULTEM™ 9085 resin, a PEI resin blend, offers robust OSU/FST properties, meets FAA requirements, and may be used in impact-resistant aerospace interior parts, ground transport applications, pellet-fed additive manufacturing/3D printing.

ULTEM™ 2300, reinforced PEI resin, with CTE close to metal, well suited for fiber optic and electrical connectors, bracketry in aerospace and automotive, enable complex designs and simplification of assembly. ULTEM™ 3473, reinforced PEI resin, 40% lighter than aluminum and may support integrated antenna filter units (AFUs) including radiofrequency (RF) filters thanks to low CTE, Surface Mount Technology (SMT) process compatibility, excellent surface metallization performance.

data.name: NORYL GTX™ Resin
data.description: NORYL GTX blends polyamide (PA) and modified polyphenylene ether polymer (PPE) technology. It combines the dimensional stability, low water absorption and heat resistance of PPE polymer with the chemical resistance and flow of PA polymer. The result is an extremely chemically resistant material with the stiffness, impact resistance and heat performance required for on-line painting. The low density of unfilled NORYL GTX resin can provide part-weight savings of up to 25% over glass or mineral filled resins.

data.name: NORYL™ Resin
data.description: The NORYL family of modified PPE resins consists of amorphous blends of PPO™ resin (polyphenylene ether) and polystyrene. They combine the inherent benefits of PPO resin (affordable high heat resistance, good electrical properties, excellent hydrolytic stability and the ability to use non-halogen FR packages), with excellent dimensional stability, good processibility and low specific gravity.NORYL resins offer a good balance of mechanical and chemical properties, and may be suitable for a wide variety of applications

data.name: LNP™ COLORCOMP™ Compound DX09911
data.description: LNP™ COLORCOMP™ Compound DX09911 is based on polycarbonate (pc) resin. This unreinforced compound features good impact resistance combined with good flow, excellent esthetics, and is colorable. It offers good processability and does not contain intentionally added PFAS. Designed for injection molding, it is suitable for various sub-industries, including automotive interiors, consumer goods, and general industrial applications.

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RVL28
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RVL28 integrates Polyamide 66 (nylon 66) resin with 40% long glass fiber and 10% PTFE, offering a blend tailored for exceptional molding ease, heat stability, wear resistance, and structural integrity. This compound is ideal for applications requiring robust mechanical properties and durability in challenging environments. It excels in automotive components, industrial machinery, and electrical housings where high performance under stress and extended wear is crucial. The addition of PTFE enhances lubricity and reduces friction, contributing to improved wear resistance and longer component lifespan. LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RVL28 facilitates efficient manufacturing processes with its excellent flow characteristics during injection molding, ensuring precision and consistency in complex part geometries.

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound UV00AS
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound UV00AS is formulated with Polyphthalamide (PPA) resin and 50% long glass fiber, offering exceptional heat stabilization and structural integrity. This compound is designed to excel in high-temperature environments, ensuring reliable performance under thermal stress. Its composition enhances dimensional stability and mechanical strength, making it suitable for demanding applications in automotive, electrical, and industrial sectors where heat resistance and robust structural properties are critical. LNP™ VERTON™ Compound UV00AS provides manufacturers with a versatile solution for components requiring both durability and thermal stability, meeting stringent performance requirements across various industries.

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RVN1AESP
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RVN1AESP features Polyamide 66 (nylon 66) resin with 50% long glass fiber and a proprietary lubricant, designed for applications requiring easy molding, wear resistance, and structural integrity. This compound is engineered to provide excellent processability in injection molding, allowing for the efficient production of complex shapes and components. Its enhanced wear resistance ensures durability in demanding environments, making it suitable for industrial machinery, automotive parts, and other applications where mechanical performance is critical. This product offers reliable performance and longevity, supported by its high stiffness and strength characteristics, contributing to the overall reliability and longevity of the finished products.

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound MV00ASXP
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound MV00ASXP utilizes polypropylene (PP) resin reinforced with 50% long glass fibers, ensuring exceptional structural integrity and stiffness. This compound is chemically coupled to enhance performance, heat stabilized for reliable operation in varying temperatures, and designed with a focus on structural applications. Ideal for automotive exteriors, water management systems, sport and leisure equipment, home appliances, and commercial appliances, LNP™ VERTON™ Compound MV00ASXP offers high stiffness and strength without the use of intentionally added PFAS. It excels in injection molding processes, providing robust solutions for industrial applications requiring durability and dimensional stability.

data.name: NORYL™ Resin WM300G
data.description: NORYL™ Resin WM300G is a non-reinforced, impact-modified blend of Polyphenylene ether (PPE) and polystyrene (PS). This resin is noted for its superior surface appearance, high ductility, low moisture absorption, and exceptional dimensional and hydrolytic stability. The use of specialized impact modification ensures improved processing stability, minimizing the risk of restricted substance formation during processing. NORYL™ Resin WM300G is ideally suited for a range of water management applications, including valves, filtration components, and water meter internals. It can be processed via injection molding and extrusion (e.g., pipe and profile applications).

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound MV006S
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound MV006S is a polypropylene (PP) resin-based compound enriched with 30% long glass fiber. Engineered to be chemically coupled, structurally robust, and heat stabilized, this material offers exceptional stiffness and strength. It is specifically designed for demanding applications in automotive exteriors, water management, sports and leisure, as well as home and commercial appliances. Its advanced formulation ensures durability and performance, making it an optimal choice for injection molding processes where strength, stability, and resistance to environmental factors are essential requirements.

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound UX03320
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound UX03320 is formulated with Polyphthalamide (PPA) resin featuring 50% long glass fiber and proprietary fillers, emphasizing structural integrity. This compound is engineered to provide exceptional strength and durability, making it suitable for applications where robust mechanical performance is essential. Its composition ensures reliable performance under demanding conditions, offering resistance to deformation and maintaining dimensional stability over time. LNP™ VERTON™ Compound UX03320 is ideal for use in automotive, industrial, and electrical components where high strength-to-weight ratio and reliability are critical, ensuring longevity and performance in challenging environments.

data.name: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RV008S
data.description: LNP™ VERTON™ Compound RV008S is a compound based on polyamide 66 (nylon 66) resin containing 40% long glass fiber. Added features include heat stabilization and structural integrity. This compound provides high stiffness and strength, making it suitable for various injection molding applications. Ideal for automotive exteriors, building components, sports and leisure equipment, home appliances, and commercial appliances, LNP VERTON RV008S ensures durability and performance across diverse industrial applications. Its enhanced structural properties and heat stabilization contribute to its reliability in demanding environments.

data.seo_title: NORYL PPX™ Resin - SABIC's Specialties Business - Knowde
data.seo_description: Knowde is the first marketplace for chemicals, polymers and ingredients. Our leading-edge digital capabilities connect thousands of sellers and buyers every day.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX630
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX630 resin is a 30% glass fiber reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade exhibits high elongation and high stiffness along with temperature performance, impact resistance, hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX630 resin is an excellent candidate for hot water system exteriors, condensate housings, and printer internals. *See NORYL PPX630F resin for NSF 61 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX630F
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX630F resin is a 30% glass fiber reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade is NSF 61 certified and exhibits high elongation and stiffness along with temperature performance, impact resistance, hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX630F resin is an excellent candidate for copper and brass replacement in water management applications such as boiler manifolds, condensers, and hydro blocks. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX640
data.description: SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL™ PPX640 resin is a 40% glass fiber reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + Polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade exhibits high stiffness along with temperature performance, impact resistance, hydrolytic stability, and dimensional stability. NORYL™ PPX640 resin is an excellent candidate for applications requiring a good chemical resistance and high stiffness.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX640F
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX640F resin is a 40% glass fiber reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade is NSF 61 certified and exhibits high elongation and stiffness along with temperature performance, impact resistance, hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX640F resin is an excellent candidate for copper and brass replacement in water management applications such as water filtration systems, boiler systems, and heat exchangers. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX7110
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX7110 resin is a non-reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + Polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade exhibits high impact resistance and good heat resistance along with hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX7110 resin is an excellent candidate for applications requiring high impact, chemical resistance, and good heat performance. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX7112
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX7112 resin is a non-reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade exhibits high modulus, high-temperature performance, and impact resistance, hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX7112 resin is an excellent candidate for exterior painted automotive applications. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX7115
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX7115 resin is a non-reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This injection moldable grade exhibits high modulus, high-temperature performance, excellent melt strength, impact resistance, hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX7115 resin is an excellent candidate for applications requiring high modulus and chemical resistance. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX7115F
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX7115F resin is a non-reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This FDA certified injection moldable grade exhibits high impact resistance and good heat resistance along with hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX7115F resin is an excellent candidate for food contact applications requiring high impact, chemical resistance, and good heat performance. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.

data.name: NORYL PPX™ Resin PPX7200U
data.description:
SABIC's Specialties Business NORYL PPX7200U resin is a non-reinforced alloy of polyphenylene ether (PPE) + polypropylene (PP). This UV-stabilized, injection moldable grade exhibits improved chemical resistance and surface esthetics along with high-temperature performance, excellent melt strength, modulus, impact resistance, hydrolytic and dimensional stability. NORYL PPX7200U resin is an excellent candidate for applications such as hot water tank components and outdoor housings and enclosures. 
This product does not contain PFAS intentionally added during SHPP’s manufacturing process and are not expected to contain unintentional PFAS impurities. Each user is responsible for evaluating the presence of unintentional PFAS impurities.
